{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013kewpeUT8GgBow5hMWTGkd","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     2→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→\n     6→  <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n     7→  <artifactId>roster</artifactId>\n     8→  <version>1.0.0</version>\n     9→  <packaging>pom</packaging>\n    10→  <name>roster</name>\n    11→\n    12→  <properties>\n    13→    <maven.compiler.release>17</maven.compiler.release>\n    14→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    15→    <liberty.version>24.0.0.12</liberty.version>\n    16→  </properties>\n    17→\n    18→  <dependencyManagement>\n    19→    <dependencies>\n    20→      <dependency>\n    21→        <groupId>io.openliberty.features</groupId>\n    22→        <artifactId>features-bom</artifactId>\n    23→        <version>${liberty.version}</version>\n    24→        <type>pom</type>\n    25→        <scope>import</scope>\n    26→      </dependency>\n    27→    </dependencies>\n    28→  </dependencyManagement>\n    29→\n    30→  <modules>\n    31→    <module>roster-common</module>\n    32→    <module>roster-ejb</module>\n    33→    <module>roster-appclient</module>\n    34→    <module>roster-web</module>\n    35→    <module>roster-ear</module>\n    36→  </modules>\n    37→\n    38→  <build>\n    39→    <pluginManagement>\n    40→      <plugins>\n    41→        <plugin>\n    42→          <groupId>io.openliberty.tools</groupId>\n    43→          <artifactId>liberty-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n    44→          <version>3.11.1</version>\n    45→        </plugin>\n    46→      </plugins>\n    47→    </pluginManagement>\n    48→  </build>\n    49→</project>\n    50→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40d6367f-f3fd-4de9-a25e-2a8ba1c4e96f","uuid":"1b50157b-b9fb-46fd-86d5-6ed3dd089b9c"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017HaWx34BTuA4uVQi4PbL6r","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→FROM maven:3.9.12-ibm-semeru-21-noble\n     2→\n     3→USER root\n     4→# install uv\n     5→RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends curl python3-venv python3-full \\\n     6→    && curl -LsSf https://astral.sh/uv/install.sh | sh\n     7→\n     8→ENV PATH=\"/root/.local/bin:$PATH\"\n     9→\n    10→# create venv and install\n    11→RUN uv venv /opt/venv \\\n    12→    && uv pip install --python /opt/venv/bin/python pytest\n    13→\n    14→ENV PATH=\"/opt/venv/bin:$PATH\"\n    15→\n    16→# Set working directory\n    17→WORKDIR /app\n    18→\n    19→# Copy all the assets\n    20→COPY . .\n    21→\n    22→RUN if [ -f smoke.py ]; then chmod +x smoke.py; fi\n    23→\n    24→RUN mvn clean install -pl roster-ear -am\n    25→\n    26→CMD [\"mvn\", \"liberty:run\", \"-pl\", \"roster-ear\"]\n    27→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40d6367f-f3fd-4de9-a25e-2a8ba1c4e96f","uuid":"e6fb18d8-dc90-4e2c-b948-dc6a87404186"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Xq7MfEw9rdDPfaGs6qvZE1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n     2→         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n     3→         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n     4→  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n     5→  \n     6→  <parent>\n     7→    <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n     8→    <artifactId>roster</artifactId>\n     9→    <version>1.0.0</version>\n    10→  </parent>\n    11→  \n    12→  <artifactId>roster-ejb</artifactId>\n    13→  <packaging>ejb</packaging>\n    14→\n    15→  <properties>\n    16→    <maven.compiler.source>17</maven.compiler.source>\n    17→    <maven.compiler.target>17</maven.compiler.target>\n    18→    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    19→  </properties>\n    20→  <name>roster-ejb</name>\n    21→\n    22→  <dependencies>\n    23→    <dependency>\n    24→      <groupId>jakarta.tutorial</groupId>\n    25→      <artifactId>roster-common</artifactId>\n    26→      <version>${project.version}</version>\n    27→    </dependency>\n    28→\n    29→    <dependency>\n    30→      <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n    31→      <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-api</artifactId>\n    32→      <version>10.0.0</version>\n    33→      <scope>provided</scope>\n    34→    </dependency>\n    35→  </dependencies>\n    36→\n    37→  <build>\n    38→  <plugins>\n    39→    <plugin>\n    40→      <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>\n    41→      <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n    42→      <version>3.13.0</version>\n    43→      <configuration>\n    44→        <annotationProcessorPaths>\n    45→          <path>\n    46→            <groupId>org.eclipse.persistence</groupId>\n    47→            <artifactId>org.eclipse.persistence.jpa.modelgen.processor</artifactId>\n    4