{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_016trvUhLfRQqyCqThRuWByt","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the full architecture. This is a Jakarta EE multi-module application (EAR + EJB + WAR + appclient) running on Open Liberty. I need to flatten it into a single Quarkus module. Here's my migration plan:\n\n1. **Flatten** multi-module into single Quarkus project\n2. **Replace** EJB `@Stateful`/`@Singleton` with CDI `@ApplicationScoped`/`@Transactional`\n3. **Keep** JPA entities (jakarta.persistence is compatible with Quarkus)\n4. **Replace** `@EJB` injection with `@Inject`\n5. **Drop** JSF beans (TeamBean, LeagueBean, PlayerBean) - not needed, REST API covers all functionality\n6. **Drop** RosterClient (appclient) - not applicable to Quarkus\n7. **Keep** JAX-RS resource with minor adaptations\n8. **Use** H2 in-memory database (same as original)\n9. **Replace** JPA Criteria Metamodel with JPQL queries (simpler for Quarkus, avoids metamodel generation)\n\nLet me start building the new project structure:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":527,"cache_read_input_tokens":61109,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":527,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":436},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40d6367f-f3fd-4de9-a25e-2a8ba1c4e96f","uuid":"b07a3233-a91e-4e04-87f3-d68fe87fc0fa"}
